cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the symbiotic relationship between humans and machines in solving problems, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The proposed areas of improvement involve artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in the form of automation of problem-solving protocols, as well as the use of knowledge communities (cs.CY) to enhance human intellect. The concept of provenance (cs.IR) is also mentioned as a means of tracking the origin and history of data and information. Finally, the automation of problem-solving protocols involves software engineering (cs.SE) techniques.
